annotation.TEXT: Whoa! I barely dodged that bullet!
Yep, here's the pass-through-able wall where FoI2's secret exit would be. But instead, there's a 1-up here.
Wow, that was kind of cool there!
Music = Win + Awesome.
Oh, man! Oh, man! Oh, man! It looks like the next level will have me facing off against The Evil Guy himself! How will this epic fight unfold?
Zwee! So, what kind of fun awaits in the second half?

But, first... I want to check out something here real quick. I'll go through the green chamber since it's pretty easy, fast, and fun. (And we get to listen to the first couple seconds of Guile's Theme multiple times!)
Alright, I didn't let the peach's double jump throw off my springboard bounces that time.
Watch out for Shotzo's shots, of course.
Hmm... I might've accidentally bounced off the saw instead there. Hey, Magikoopa? Can you maybe spawn a little further away from the saw?
LOL. Thanks, peach. Thanks a whole bunch. But, I can just wall jump up using the peach, so there's that.
Ah, there we go. I often like stomping a koopa and then immediately frying the shell-less koopa and the shell simultaneously like that.
Alright, it's time to enter The Space Hideout!

Oh, what? Okay, I was just checking to see if Shotzos are edible, which they aren't. But, what the heck with that hit I took? My head didn't appear to even touch that bullet, and it's able to damage me while I'm riding Yoshi? Really, game?
I bet those balls of fire there weren't actually line-guided, but instead going around invisible solid-only-for-enemies custom blocks.
And, unfortunately, I have to say "Bye, Yoshi!" here, because this hack won't let me take him out of the level.
There's a Bullet Bird cannon there, probably just in case I destroyed all of the koopas without fully feeding Yoshi.
Hmm... Do I want that flower? ...I'm gonna say "no" this time. I have a feeling the peach will be more useful in this room, due to the presence of saws.
D'oh! That's definitely not what I wanted to do.
That ? block is guarded by lightning.
Whoa, geez! Okay, you can spin jump bounce off those gigaspeed bullets! Good to know! (I wasn't going to intentionally test for that, but it happened by chance there!)
Push!
Whoa, that cannon on wheels fires really fast shots! (I think it looks like an Autobomb from SMB2, so that's what I'll call it from now on.)
Huh, that guide line must be close enough to the slope there to cause this oddity with the saw reversing direction at the lower-right corner there.
Well, this room went very well, thanks in part to the peach giving me additional maneuverability at key moments.
Huh... Is it just me, or does the layout of the walls here seem familiar?
Oh, god... Did I just make the level unwinnable and will I have to use a space-time rewind here?
Oh, man. Gotta dodge munchers here.
This is getting trickier and trickier...
Alright, Yoshi's fed up with all of YouTube's glitches...
GOOOOOAAAAALLLLL!!!!! I wonder if maybe the goal sphere sprite replaced that last Shotzo's sprite...
Also, I've gotta worry about those Autobombs and their ludicrous speed bullets as well. (Huh, they actually move kind of like Birdo, so I almost want to call them Autobirdos now...)
There's another single-use springboard, which I probably don't need as long as I have the peach, but I should at least try to do this part properly.
WHOOAAAA!!! That reminds me of that huge springboard in Mario's Search For His Hat.
Whoa, man. Good thing there was enough room for me to stand to the left of the pillar there.
Whoa! Gotta be careful of Autowhatever's (yeah, I'm calling it "Autowhatever" now) supersonic bullets, of course.
Whoa, that was close!
Uh, oh. Lightning. I'm gonna have to jump through at the right time.
Of course, the enemies are different, there are no ice blocks, and this place isn't underwater, among a few other things, but I can still totally recognize the FoI2 resemblance here!
Maybe not, actually, thanks to that ledge that Yoshi landed on, which I might be able to shell jump to...
Ooh, peachy! And, now that I can wall jump, anything up this wall?
Okay, so I have to stay far, far away from Shotzo's bullets, since their hitboxes are way larger than the bullets' apparent sizes.
Okay, good enough. I clearly bounced off of Magikoopa that time.

Oh, it leads to the far left of this switch area, which has a leftward pointing arrow and I assume a side exit. (I was assuming that I'd be sent back to the starting room that had the four doors, but this is fine, too.)
At least Magikoopa's still shell-killable.
BGM: Touhou 5 - The Grimoire of Alice
Find out next time, on what won't quite be the finale, since I'll still have the special world to do after this! To be continued...
Haw, haw!
Alright, now where does the door that replaces the already-pressed green switch here lead?
Gotta get the timing on the Thwomp and the Shotzo's bullets synched up properly here.
"Tick" Graze +1.
Unfortunately, there's just no reaching that last coin without an athletic peach. That's probably gonna bother people's OCDs so much...
Interestingly, those Autowhatever cannons on wheels are stomp-killable.
Alright, no more pirate talk. So, I guess I should duck here, right? ...Yep.
Careful here. I wouldn't want Yoshi to fall into that boiling gatorade.
Okay, now that I'm on land that it's okay to spin jump on, I want to see if I can at least safely bounce off of Magikoopa. (This is risking my peach, of course.)
The turn blocks spell out "SMW" here, which is cool.
Uh, oh. Turn blocks galore. Does that mean Magikoopa? ...Yep, that means Magikoopa.
Doesn't look like it. Well, let's start dodging and/or spin jumping off of saws over here, I guess.
Well, there you go! I somehow got the double-grab to work there!
Ooh, I chose the correct path there. Huh, did that Shotzo above me just vanish?
Awesome! Once again, thank you, peach!
There's another reset door, probably just in case I didn't bring the second springboard, or wasted it.
Hmm... Seeing how there are flammable and inflammable enemies here, I think I will take the flower this time.
Just look at that moon's evil smirk. Hello, and welcome back to Something else! Today, I'll be taking on The Space Hideout!
Avast! Thar be smashin' pillars here!
...Yeah! A lot of the terrain here is shaped the same way as part of the original game's Forest of Illusion 2!
Alright, Yoshi's fed up with the trolls that keep releasing many of Twitch's Pokémon on Pokémon Black, and...
There's another peach. Unfortunately, it's of no use to me right now since my current peach is still intact.
Arrr, matey. We be autoscrollin' here.
And I just massacred all the duders that were there. (That would've been neat if I somehow pulled off a 1-up combo there, but I guess there wasn't quite enough stuff to stomp.)
Yikes! Thank you, peach! (No, I'm not thanking the princess here. I'm thanking the fruit that gives me the ability to double-jump.)
Oh, I just thought of something! The peach's double jump cancels spin jumps, so I can totally abuse that fact here!
Oh, what's this red springboard do?
Oh, and there's another one. Let's see... Can I double-grab them? ...It's gonna be tricky, because of how springboards are.
Whoa. I really don't feel like testing if Shotzo or its bullets are slide-killable right now. Also, there's a single-use springboard, so yeah, this has totally gotta be a screw-up-able puzzle.
Yeah, awesome! ...And there's a hidden 1-up here as well. So, it appears this blue Yoshi sprouted some wings when he grew up. Was there perhaps some Red Bull in those koopas he ate?
Wait, does Magikoopa have spikes on his head? Oh, man. So, Spikitu's been giving out his headgear to other bad guys, I guess. (Obviously, I probably shouldn't try to stomp Magikoopa now.)
Whoops, that wasn't exactly what I was trying to do, but whatever.
There we... go...
Whoa, a blue egg? Hi, Yoshi! Let's get you fed up!
"Tick" Graze +1.
Push! (I was kind of pushing it on time there, too.)

"R"... So, either the game wants me to scroll the screen to the right, or... more than likely, there's a screw-up-able puzzle here and that's a reset door. Also, there's a Shotzo from the Kirby series there. I'm going to try to avoid it and its bullets.
